      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Phenol, C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>5</sub>OH, is a stronger acid than methanol, CH<sub>3</sub>OH, even though both contain an O–H bond. Draw the structures of the anions resulting from loss of H<sup>+</sup> from phenol and methanol, and use resonance structures to explain the difference in acidity.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcG9RIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--d754c27f475dea5dbd050aa5519324a29bc5bc10/OChem_02_EC_027.jpg\" alt=\"The structures of phenol and methanol with their respective p K a values, 9.89 and 15.54.\">",
